[1] Poland: (Podlaskie) domestic swine
Date: Wed, 23 Jul 2014
Source: Reuters [edited]
http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/07/23/us-poland-pork-ministry-asf-idUSKBN0FS1LG20140723


Poland confirms case of African swine fever in farm pigs
--------------------------------------------------------
Polish authorities have identified the country's 1st ever case of African swine fever (ASF) to be found in farm pigs, the chief veterinary officer said on Wednesday [23 Jul 2014; see comment]. Previous cases of ASF, in wild boars, promoted Russia and China to impose restrictions on Polish pork exports, causing a fall in domestic pork prices.

"This is the 1st case of ASF in farm pigs in Poland," chief veterinary officer Marek Pirsztuk told Reuters. "The area lies 3-6 km [1.8-3.7 mi] from the border with Belarus." He also said that about 200 farm pigs from the danger zone of 7 km (4.3 miles) around the county of Grodek [in Podlaskie voivodeship, 1st level administrative division] may have to be put down. This is the same area where 9 cases of ASF in wild boars were identified earlier this year [2014]. Pirsztuk added in a statement that the case of ASF had been identified in a farm with 5 pigs. 2 of them died and the remaining 3 have been put down. The farm has been disinfected, he said.

According to the World Organisation for Animal Health (OIE) there is so far no effective vaccine against ASF, but the disease poses no danger to human health.

[byline: Anna Wlodarcza, Marcin Goettig]

