[Poland's ASF follow-up report no 8, covering the outbreak above in a small holding of domestic swine, was submitted on 23 Jul 2014 and is available, with a map, at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=15686.

According to OIE's outbreak summary, since the start of the event in Poland (reportedly on 18 Jun 2014) and as of 23 Jul 2014, the total number of (submitted) outbreaks is 8 (7 in wild boar, 1 in domestic swine), and the summarised statistical data are as follows:

Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Wild boar / not available / 22 / 22 / 0 / 0
Swine [domestic] / 8 / 5 / 5 / 3 / 0
(See at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/temp/reports/en_fup_0000015686_20140724_182853.pdf)

Poland's interpretation pertaining the official number and status of outbreaks according to EU criteria is included in ProMED-mail posting 20140709.2598113. - Mod.AS

